ance of commitment, a flexible attitude, a strong sense of identity, a support network, a sense of perspective, and a sense of humor. They also reveal the benefits of these marriages, including a greater appreciation for Japanese ways and the opportunity to continually grow and learn. Based on extensive research, the book provides a new look at Japan from the unique perspective of those American women most intimately involved with its culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aInterracial marriagezJapan. 0aInterracial marriagezUnited States. 0aJapanese American families. 0aJapanese AmericansxMarriage customs and rites. 0aMenzJapanxAttitudes. 0aWomen, WhitezUnited StatesxAttitudes. 4aSociology : Comparative Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2016z978311149098440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079149010540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791490105423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791490105/original  a978-3-11-149098-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles